# Geba, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Geba (; Dargwa: Гьеба) is a rural locality (a selo) in Akushinsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 735 as of 2010. There are 8 streets.
Geography
Geba is located 13&nbsp;km southeast of Akusha (the district's administrative centre) by road, on the Dargolakotta River. Kurkimakhi is the nearest rural locality.
